cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "llm-memory-eval: A Reproducible Evaluation Harness for Summarization-Based Memory and Retrieval-Augmented Generation"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: 2026-05-21
authors:
  - family-names: Okeke
    given-names: Abuchi
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"
license: MIT
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX
repository-code: "https://github.com/okekeag/llm-memory-eval"
abstract: >-
  llm-memory-eval is an open-source Python package that operationalizes a
  comparative repeated-measures evaluation of Summarization-Based Memory
  (recursive abstractive summarization performed by the base LLM) and
  Retrieval-Augmented Generation (dense embeddings with FAISS over chunked
  context) on three long-context benchmarks (LongBench, LoCoMo, and
  LongMemEval). The harness provides config-driven backends (Ollama,
  Together AI, AWS Bedrock, Hugging Face Inference Endpoints, and any
  OpenAI-compatible endpoint), deterministic decoding controls, and a full
  statistical pipeline (paired t-tests, Wilcoxon, two-way ANOVA with
  Holm-Bonferroni and simple-effects post-hoc analysis) that reproduces the
  results reported in the underlying dissertation.
keywords:
  - large-language-models
  - retrieval-augmented-generation
  - summarization
  - long-context-evaluation
  - longbench
  - locomo
  - longmemeval
  - reproducible-research
